Israeli Stocks: Hadera, Financial Levers, XTL Biopharmaceuticals

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-04-21T12:20:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/israeli-stocks-hadera-paper-financial-levers-advance.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index advanced 0.2
percent to 1,341.89 at the 2:45 p.m. close in Tel Aviv, the
highest level on record. Investors traded about 946.2 million
shekels ($278 million) in shares and convertible securities.
Today’s trading session was shortened for the Passover holiday.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Hadera Paper Ltd. (HAP)   climbed to the highest since
March 8, gaining 2.2 percent to 275 shekels. The maker of paper
products received a temporary permit valid until May 30 that
will allow for the flow of wastewater into the Hadera River.  Financial Levers Ltd. (LVR)   rose the most since March 1,
increasing 3.4 percent to 1.058 shekels. The investment company
received a report on the economic potential of the Yam
discovery, one of the oil drilling sites in its Shemen project.
Netherland Sewell & Associates Inc., an oil and gas consulting
company, said the gross mean resources at the site is estimated
at 142.4 million barrels.  XTL Biopharmaceuticals Ltd. (XTLB)   gained to the highest
in more than two weeks, rising 6.2 percent to 0.637 shekel. The
biopharmaceutical company sought orphan drug status for its
myeloma drug from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
